## Offset Management

### Automatic Offset Commits (Default)

The consumer automatically commits offsets periodically:

```java
// Enable automatic commits (default behavior)
props.setProperty("enable.auto.commit", "true");
props.setProperty("auto.commit.interval.ms", "1000");

KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props);
consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));

while (running) {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
    for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
        // Process record - offset automatically committed after interval
    }
}
```

**Auto-Commit Semantics**:
- Commits happen **in the background** at `auto.commit.interval.ms` intervals
- Only offsets from fully processed batches are committed
- **Exactly-once semantics are NOT guaranteed** if processing fails between poll and commit

### Manual Offset Commits

For precise control over when records are considered consumed:

```java
props.setProperty("enable.auto.commit", "false");

KafkaConsumer<String, String> consumer = new KafkaConsumer<>(props);
consumer.subscribe(Arrays.asList("topic"));

while (running) {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofMillis(100));
    try {
        for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
            processRecord(record);
        }
        // Commit only after processing completes
        consumer.commitSync();
    } catch (ProcessingException e) {
        // Don't commit - record will be reprocessed on restart
        handleError(e);
    }
}
```

#### Synchronous Commits

```java
// Commit all records from last poll()
void commitSync()

// Commit with custom timeout
void commitSync(Duration timeout)

// Commit specific offsets
void commitSync(Map<TopicPartition, OffsetAndMetadata> offsets)
void commitSync(Map<TopicPartition, OffsetAndMetadata> offsets, Duration timeout)
```

**Semantics**:
- **Blocking**: Waits for broker response or timeout
- **Atomic**: All offsets commit together
- **Safe**: Retried internally for transient failures
- **Exceptions**: `CommitFailedException` if group rebalances before commit completes

**Timeout Behavior**:
```java
// Use default timeout from config (default.api.timeout.ms)
consumer.commitSync();

// Custom timeout
consumer.commitSync(Duration.ofSeconds(30));
```

#### Asynchronous Commits

```java
// Fire-and-forget commit
void commitAsync()

// Commit with callback for success/failure
void commitAsync(OffsetCommitCallback callback)

// Commit specific offsets
void commitAsync(Map<TopicPartition, OffsetAndMetadata> offsets,
                 OffsetCommitCallback callback)
```

**Semantics**:
- **Non-blocking**: Returns immediately
- **Ordered**: Multiple async commits maintain order
- **Callback guarantee**: Previous callbacks invoked before `commitSync()` completes
- **Exceptions**: Passed to callback or silently discarded if no callback

**Callback Pattern**:
```java
consumer.commitAsync((offsets, exception) -> {
    if (exception != null) {
        log.error("Commit failed for offsets: " + offsets, exception);
    } else {
        log.debug("Committed offsets: " + offsets);
    }
});
```

### Offset Commit Format

**Critical Semantic**: The committed offset should be the offset of the **next record to read**, not the last record read.

```java
// WRONG - commits last offset read, will skip next record
for (ConsumerRecord<String, String> record : records) {
    process(record);
    consumer.commitSync(Collections.singletonMap(
        record.topic(),
        new OffsetAndMetadata(record.offset())  // WRONG!
    ));
}

// CORRECT - use nextOffsets() or offset + 1
consumer.commitSync(records.nextOffsets());

// ALSO CORRECT - explicit offset + 1 per partition
for (TopicPartition partition : records.partitions()) {
    long lastOffset = records.records(partition).get(
        records.records(partition).size() - 1
    ).offset();
    consumer.commitSync(Collections.singletonMap(
        partition,
        new OffsetAndMetadata(lastOffset + 1)
    ));
}
```

### Querying Committed Offsets

```java
// Query for specific partitions
Map<TopicPartition, OffsetAndMetadata> committed(Set<TopicPartition> partitions)

// With custom timeout
Map<TopicPartition, OffsetAndMetadata> committed(
    Set<TopicPartition> partitions,
    Duration timeout)
```

**Return Value**:
- Maps partition to `OffsetAndMetadata` (offset + metadata)
- Returns `null` for partitions with no prior commit
- Includes leader epoch for log truncation detection

