## Error Handling

### Exception Hierarchy

```
KafkaException (root)
├── CommitFailedException
│   └── Unrecoverable: group rebalanced before commit
│
├── OffsetOutOfRangeException
│   └── Position outside valid range: seek failed
│
├── InvalidOffsetException
│   └── No offset defined for partition
│
├── LogTruncationException
│   └── Log was truncated: leader epoch mismatch
│
└── WakeupException
    └── Consumer interrupted by wakeup() call
```

### Common Exceptions and Recovery

#### CommitFailedException

```
Occurs: During commitSync() when group has rebalanced
Cause: Processing took longer than max.poll.interval.ms
        or consumer failed and rejoined with new assignment

Recovery:
- Catch exception
- Not retriable: partitions already reassigned
- Prevent by: call poll() frequently enough (see max.poll.interval.ms)
```

**Example**:
```java
try {
    consumer.commitSync();
} catch (CommitFailedException e) {
    // Partition likely reassigned
    log.error("Commit failed - group rebalanced: " + e.getMessage());

    // Get new assignment and continue
    Set<TopicPartition> assignment = consumer.assignment();
    if (assignment.isEmpty()) {
        log.error("No partitions assigned - waiting for rebalance");
    }
    // Next poll() will handle reassignment
}
```

#### OffsetOutOfRangeException

```
Occurs: When seeking to or polling from invalid offset
Cause: Offset < log start or > log end
       Log compaction removed messages
       Requested offset no longer exists

Recovery:
- Seek to valid offset: seekToBeginning() or seekToEnd()
- Or set auto.offset.reset=earliest/latest
- Or commitSync() to reset to last committed offset
```

**Example**:
```java
try {
    consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));
} catch (OffsetOutOfRangeException e) {
    log.warn("Offset out of range, seeking to beginning: " + e.getMessage());
    consumer.seekToBeginning(consumer.assignment());
}
```

#### InvalidOffsetException

```
Occurs: When calling position() with undefined offset
Cause: Partition assigned but no position set yet
       No committed offset and auto.offset.reset=none

Recovery:
- Seek explicitly
- Or set auto.offset.reset=earliest/latest
- Or call poll() to initialize position
```

#### WakeupException

```
Occurs: When wakeup() called during blocking operation
Cause: External thread called consumer.wakeup()
Action: Propagates to calling thread's poll() or other blocking operation

Recovery:
- Catch and exit loop
- Call close() to cleanup
- Signal shutdown to other threads
```

**Example** (See [Multi-threaded Processing](#multi-threaded-processing) for full example):
```java
try {
    ConsumerRecords<String, String> records = consumer.poll(Duration.ofSeconds(1));
    // process records
} catch (WakeupException e) {
    // Shutdown gracefully
    log.info("Consumer woken up, shutting down");
} finally {
    consumer.close();
}
```

#### LogTruncationException

```
Occurs: When reading transactional messages with read_committed
Cause: Producer's transaction was rolled back
       Log was truncated on partition leader
       Committed offset is no longer valid

Recovery:
- Seek to valid offset
- Reset position to earliest/latest
- Investigate broker/producer for issues
```

